8.Given an array arr, use selection sort to sort arr[] in increasing order.
Platform : GeeksForGeeks
SOURCE CODE : class Solution {
    public void selectionSort(int[] arr) {

        int n = arr.length;

        for (int i = 0; i < n - 1; i++) {

            int minIndex = i;

            for (int j = i + 1; j < n; j++) {

                if (arr[j] < arr[minIndex]) {
                    minIndex = j;
                }
            }

            int temp = arr[minIndex];
            arr[minIndex] = arr[i];
            arr[i] = temp;
        }
    }
}
Link : https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/problems/selection-sort/1
9.Given an array arr[] of positive integers.The task is to complete the insertsort() function which is used to implement Insertion Sort.
Platform : GeeksForGeeks
SOURCE CODE : class Solution {
    public void insertionSort(int[] arr) {

        int n = arr.length;

        for (int i = 1; i < n; i++) {

            int key = arr[i];
            int j = i - 1;
              
            while (j >= 0 && arr[j] > key) {
                arr[j + 1] = arr[j];
                j--;
            }

            arr[j + 1] = key;
        }
    }
}
